ts show a normal hemoglobin level, which is good, so it's not anemia causing the bleeding.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036298,0.072353,0.097089,0.10593,0.11323,0.10944,0.1006,0.09122,0.08352,0.075607,0.066441,0.04828],"unified_progress":[0.041051,0.076258,0.090786,0.096034,0.1029,0.099366,0.098763,0.096265,0.091341,0.086714,0.072517,0.048006]},{"section":6,"text":"The platelet count is 200,000/mL. Wait, that's actually within the normal range because normal platelets are usually around 150,000 to 450,000.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029685,0.070925,0.10543,0.12047,0.13286,0.12724,0.13557,0.084141,0.068047,0.051382,0.04215,0.032104],"unified_progress":[0.040543,0.082856,0.10129,0.10758,0.11284,0.10519,0.11621,0.08771,0.079054,0.068273,0.058342,0.040106]},{"section":7,"text":"So platelets aren't the issue here.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041004,0.075706,0.095213,0.10673,0.11336,0.11142,0.12149,0.089282,0.076328,0.06771,0.058048,0.043698],"unified_progress":[0.040874,0.075235,0.091164,0.10133,0.10563,0.10125,0.11085,0.092891,0.084715,0.080149,0.067103,0.04881]},{"section":8,"text":"Next, the PT (prothrombin time) and PPT (partial thromboplastin time) are normal.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034107,0.068646,0.095236,0.11304,0.12005,0.11904,0.12081,0.095243,0.077559,0.062741,0.052344,0.041179],"unified_progress":[0.039087,0.076558,0.094989,0.10631,0.10994,0.10467,0.10738,0.09198,0.087939,0.073,0.0614,0.046742]},{"section":9,"text":"That rules out issues with the extrinsic clotting pathway because those tests are part of that pathway.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039717,0.059277,0.080721,0.093112,0.10394,0.10786,0.10963,0.1024,0.094689,0.083809,0.071229,0.05363],"unified_progress":[0.040077,0.065527,0.082719,0.092634,0.10054,0.10581,0.10436,0.09978,0.09386,0.089696,0.072858,0.05215]},{"section":10,"text":"So the problem isn't in the body's response to clotting factors from outside the blood.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038283,0.059763,0.077551,0.087954,0.096156,0.101,0.10313,0.10183,0.098213,0.091939,0.081188,0.062993],"unified_progress":[0.040354,0.064885,0.079318,0.088404,0.096064,0.099849,0.10075,0.10055,0.097365,0.095414,0.07942,0.057622]},{"section":11,"text":"Now, the bleeding time is elevated.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041385,0.072962,0.088016,0.098397,0.10318,0.10342,0.10367,0.093211,0.086093,0.07937,0.071463,0.058828],"unified_progress":[0.042288,0.074938,0.088516,0.097681,0.10127,0.098486,0.099575,0.093393,0.091042,0.08301,0.072137,0.057668]},{"section":12,"text":"That suggests a problem with the intrinsic clotting mechanism.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042201,0.063717,0.083326,0.095428,0.10338,0.10518,0.10676,0.096858,0.089792,0.081965,0.070739,0.06066],"unified_progress":[0.042738,0.069526,0.086016,0.095133,0.10006,0.10187,0.10228,0.095774,0.091027,0.084499,0.073054,0.058015]},{"section":13,"text":"The factor VIII level is reduced, and the ristocetin cofactor assay is also low.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032649,0.062467,0.088528,0.10509,0.11373,0.11526,0.11428,0.099649,0.085533,0.071328,0.061107,0.05037],"unified_progress":[0.038872,0.074016,0.092037,0.10226,0.10741,0.10386,0.10265,0.093365,0.091077,0.076735,0.065198,0.052512]},{"section":14,"text":"Ristocetin cofactor (RCA) is part of the von Willebrand factor (VWF) complex.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030693,0.054194,0.074984,0.088501,0.10383,0.11065,0.11201,0.10957,0.10172,0.085828,0.069165,0.058858],"unified_progress":[0.035383,0.064201,0.084108,0.096521,0.10149,0.11787,0.10578,0.099305,0.092328,0.08369,0.067534,0.051783]},{"section":15,"text":"So if both factor VIII and RCA are low, it points towards a deficiency in VWF.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041155,0.05501,0.075186,0.087456,0.098556,0.10295,0.10507,0.10059,0.095686,0.087823,0.078096,0.072427],"unified_progress":[0.042761,0.065685,0.081889,0.091999,0.097661,0.10141,0.10016,0.096939,0.092657,0.085875,0.07691,0.066053]},{"section":16,"text":"Von Willebrand disease is a bleeding disorder characterized by a deficiency or dysfunction of the VWF, which is necessary for normal platelet function and blood clotting.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022794,0.043099,0.063523,0.077525,0.096895,0.10742,0.11163,0.11706,0.11388,0.097071,0.078335,0.070759],"unified_progress":[0.027607,0.055115,0.080206,0.09337,0.10028,0.11436,0.10856,0.105,0.097853,0.090434,0.07198,0.055238]},{"section":17,"text":"There are different types, like type I and type II, but the presentation here fits a type I or II von Willebrand disease.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030289,0.050885,0.066224,0.077405,0.089528,0.097397,0.10329,0.10743,0.10681,0.10149,0.088743,0.080512],"unified_progress":[0.035591,0.06126,0.076972,0.089487,0.095014,0.10125,0.10112,0.1014,0.097021,0.092946,0.080013,0.067933]},{"section":18,"text":"Since the platelet count is normal and the PT/PPT are normal, the issue is specifically with the VWF.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038303,0.051681,0.071787,0.082412,0.091756,0.095452,0.09651,0.094296,0.093466,0.091468,0.093507,0.099362],"unified_progress":[0.040882,0.062331,0.075428,0.083431,0.089894,0.092223,0.092493,0.093762,0.093765,0.091012,0.09255,0.092229]},{"section":19,"text":"The easy bruising and prolonged bleeding after minor injuries are classic symptoms of this condition.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049281,0.066886,0.070855,0.075644,0.077928,0.082183,0.085523,0.089834,0.092382,0.094313,0.099681,0.11549],"unified_progre