,0.02984]},{"section":4,"text":"His lab results show a hemoglobin of 14.5 g/dL, which is normal for a young male.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053228,0.10725,0.13727,0.13642,0.12725,0.10394,0.086027,0.070239,0.05827,0.047574,0.039597,0.032939],"unified_progress":[0.051117,0.092864,0.10752,0.10583,0.11107,0.10093,0.09233,0.087711,0.079224,0.06845,0.058939,0.04401]},{"section":5,"text":"Platelets are at 200,000/mL, which is within the normal range as well.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037077,0.094268,0.13333,0.14612,0.13061,0.10928,0.089058,0.073107,0.060707,0.05016,0.041944,0.034336],"unified_progress":[0.04495,0.088118,0.10561,0.11028,0.11443,0.10438,0.11619,0.084303,0.075413,0.06409,0.05431,0.03794]},{"section":6,"text":"His PT and PTT are normal, so that rules out some common clotting factor deficiencies like vitamin K deficiency or liver disease, which usually affect these tests.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042357,0.082565,0.10119,0.11337,0.11261,0.10697,0.099421,0.088923,0.079014,0.068482,0.057687,0.047416],"unified_progress":[0.039598,0.075993,0.094502,0.10379,0.1084,0.1058,0.10869,0.09348,0.086571,0.075017,0.062341,0.045819]},{"section":7,"text":"But then, the bleeding time is elevated.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035317,0.068582,0.087006,0.093075,0.10168,0.102,0.097026,0.094592,0.088568,0.089837,0.076629,0.06569],"unified_progress":[0.04331,0.078702,0.090024,0.10135,0.10142,0.099295,0.099694,0.09393,0.087351,0.085567,0.068915,0.050444]},{"section":8,"text":"Bleeding time is a measure of how long it takes for a small cut to stop bleeding, and it's often used to assess platelet function.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047261,0.071574,0.085713,0.094619,0.098917,0.098835,0.098552,0.095105,0.09042,0.082369,0.073447,0.063188],"unified_progress":[0.044544,0.073735,0.08888,0.096239,0.10148,0.10191,0.10055,0.095032,0.090559,0.082205,0.070588,0.054287]},{"section":9,"text":"Elevated bleeding time suggests a problem with platelets or maybe von Willebrand disease, which affects both platelet adhesion and the clotting process.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041248,0.059405,0.07582,0.088065,0.09842,0.10254,0.10448,0.10278,0.098167,0.088002,0.076729,0.064347],"unified_progress":[0.041403,0.069463,0.08776,0.095876,0.10222,0.10532,0.10488,0.096115,0.090242,0.082623,0.07039,0.053705]},{"section":10,"text":"The factor VIII level is reduced, and the ristocetin cofactor assay is also low.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027103,0.059459,0.081457,0.095692,0.10547,0.10814,0.10663,0.1016,0.09589,0.085256,0.073285,0.060026],"unified_progress":[0.037386,0.074738,0.093581,0.10274,0.10846,0.10562,0.10775,0.09392,0.088023,0.077295,0.06382,0.046665]},{"section":11,"text":"Factor VIII is a key component in the clotting cascade, and von Willebrand factor (vWF) is what binds to factor VIII and helps it function.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032712,0.058125,0.077005,0.093389,0.10453,0.10865,0.10786,0.10373,0.097007,0.084771,0.072256,0.059961],"unified_progress":[0.040921,0.075918,0.094255,0.10254,0.10826,0.10563,0.11049,0.092679,0.08485,0.075003,0.06316,0.046291]},{"section":12,"text":"Ristocetin is an antibiotic that can induce the binding of vWF to platelets, so a low ristocetin cofactor assay suggests a problem with vWF.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027524,0.054293,0.074241,0.090841,0.10353,0.10895,0.10903,0.10616,0.10072,0.088296,0.075295,0.061128],"unified_progress":[0.03823,0.073643,0.092251,0.10092,0.1074,0.10578,0.11182,0.093976,0.085735,0.077582,0.06507,0.047588]},{"section":13,"text":"Putting this together, the reduced factor VIII and low ristocetin cofactor assay point towards von Willebrand disease.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026832,0.052647,0.06978,0.083557,0.09397,0.098592,0.098769,0.097852,0.095245,0.09394,0.092234,0.096581],"unified_progress":[0.034055,0.064994,0.080758,0.090195,0.095497,0.096106,0.10177,0.091777,0.088493,0.084011,0.085337,0.087009]},{"section":14,"text":"This is because von Willebrand factor is necessary for the proper function of factor VIII.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03575,0.055119,0.071262,0.084902,0.095458,0.10067,0.10331,0.10296,0.099896,0.09299,0.083416,0.074265],"unified_progress":[0.041196,0.069577,0.085749,0.095046,0.10068,0.10108,0.10455,0.094662,0.089937,0.082939,0.074022,0.060559]},{"section":15,"text":"In von Willebrand disease, there's either a deficiency of vWF or it doesn't work properly, leading to issues with platelet adhesion and clot formation.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037552,0.053773,0.06881,0.08156,0.093898,0.10042,0.10511,0.10591,0.10342,0.094431,0.083848,0.071273],"unified_progress":[0.041153,0.068726,0.085819,0.094505,0.10101,0.10417,0.10498,0.096451,0.090852,0.083732,0.072289,0.056307]},{"section":16,"text":"This would explain the prolonged bleeding times and the symptoms of easy bruising and nosebleeds.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04628,0.070044,0.072361,0.072818,0.079487,0.082979,0.087925,0.092149,0.093519,0.091126,0.10248,0.10884],"unified_progress":[0.070359,0.096148,0.087128,0.084273,0.084618,0.08851,0.0851,0.089158,0.084374,0.080387,0.077529,0.072416]},{"section":17,"text":"Other possibilities could include platelet function disorders, but those usually don't affect factor VIII levels.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030416,0.049386,0.066958,0.077901,0.090155,0.096846,0.10264,0.10594,0.10619,0.10368,0.092137,0.077756],"unified_progress":[0.040091,0.067239,0.085598,0.09261,0.097708,0.098943,0.098922,0.095775,0.093052,0.091137,0.077717,0.061206]},{"section":18,"text":"Since factor VIII is low and the ristocetin assay is also low, it's more likely a problem with the von Willebrand factor itself.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024632,0.047793,0.065764,0.079717,0.092009,0.098948,0.10322,0.10505,0.10532,0.10026,0.093124,0.084157],"unified_progress":[0.034788,0.066172,0.083061,0.091071,0.09781,0.099232,0.09933,0.095454,0.092542,0.087861,0.081474,0.071207]},{"section":19,"text":"So, the most likely diagnosis here is von Willebrand disease.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02231,0.037726,0.048011,0.055297,0.063784,0.070125,0.076034,0.084818,0.091834,0.11847,0.14267,0.18892],"unified_progress":[0.021699,0.038933,0.048626,0.059778,0.064105,0.074239,0.077008,0.089233,0.097504,0.10619,0.13788,0.1848]},{"section":20,"text":"The patient's symptoms of easy bruising and prolonged bleeding, along with elevated bleeding time and reduced factor VIII and ristocetin cofactor levels, point to von Willebrand disease.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027742,0.047019,0.051949,0.055921,0.063893,0.069944,0.077028,0.085643,0.093811,0.10775,0.14216,0.17714],"unified_progress":[0.039172,0.058352,0.058038,0.060423,0.065001,0.072896,0.075177,0.086547,0.093909,0.1008,0.12551,0.16417]},{"section":21,"text":"This condition is characterized by a deficiency or dysfunction of von Willebrand factor, which is essential for proper platelet adhesion and clotting.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034491,0.047214,0.05843,0.068631,0.079079,0.086412,0.094613,0.10069,0.10452,0.10659,0.10803,0.1113],"unified_progress":[0.035849,0.055517,0.069528,0.076648,0.083648,0.089482,0.092403,0.09488,0.098058,0.0983,0.1014,0.10429]},{"section":22,"text":"<answer> von Willebrand disease </answer>","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02955,0.048304,0.063939,0.07227,0.083858,0.089829